summary: Qualified lawyer with post-graduate specialization degree in Environmental Law and LL.M. in Public International Law. Significant experience working in the Public International sector, including research and preparation of statements of grounds and methods of implementation of International Maritime Instruments and International Treaties. Practical first-hand experience on bilateral and multilateral State negotiations and conferences acting as a liaison between the maritime community and policy makers, seeking to develop a career focused on the protection of the marine environment
